&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this position, you will use your consulting and project delivery skills to enable organizations to leverage their investment in location intelligence. You will work alongside Senior Consultants and Practice Managers to recommend relevant strategies, architectures, and solutions for customer requirements. You will partner directly with customers to prepare them for enterprise implementations, migrations, and change management activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This team supports all aspects of our Federal engagement delivery, with a focus on Earth Sciences &amp;amp; Enviroment agencies. You will be part of a talented cross-functional team of technical consultants, system engineers, software developers, and configuration specialists delivering capabilities that enable our customers to make a difference in communities around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Professional Services division is the consulting and implementation arm of Esri. We break ground in new markets, push the technology envelope, and ultimately deliver transformational solutions to high-profile clients worldwide. The Professional Services organization is comprised of nearly 1,000 talented business and technical professionals who strive every day to help our users be successful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Esri has a Relocation Assistance Program and can provide support with relocating to the Vienna, VA area for this position.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
